  "text": "The Firefox Servo CSS style system integration forms a key pipeline for style resolution and application to DOM elements. The core components are located in `layout/style/` under the mozilla-firefox/firefox repository:\n\n1. **ServoStyleSet** (layout/style/ServoStyleSet.h and .cpp): The main entry point for Gecko-to-Servo style resolution. The ServoStyleSet class (defined at line 107 in the header) orchestrates the overall style system, managing stylesheet data and initiating style computations.\n\n2. **RestyleManager** (layout/style/RestyleManager.h): The component responsible for scheduling and managing style recalculation. The RestyleManager class (defined at line 202 in the header) tracks DOM changes that trigger restyles, maintains element snapshots for invalidation, and coordinates the restyle process with the layout system.\n\n3. **ServoBindings** (layout/style/ServoBindings.h): Provides Gecko-to-Servo FFI declarations. This header defines C FFI functions (prefixed with Servo_) that enable C++ code to call into the Rust-based Servo engine. Key FFI function patterns include Servo_StyleSet_*, Servo_CssRules_*, and rule-specific functions generated via macros.\n\n4. **ServoUtils** (layout/style/ServoUtils.h): Utility functions for Servo traversal state management. Declares critical functions like InitializeServo(), ShutdownServo(), and IsInServoTraversal() that coordinate between Gecko's main thread and the Servo parallel traversal.\n\n5. **moz.build** (layout/style/moz.build): The build configuration file that lists all source files in the style system. It includes EXPORTS declarations for all public headers (including ServoStyleSet.h, ServoBindings.h, RestyleManager.h, ServoUtils.h) and UNIFIED_SOURCES for compilation (RestyleManager.cpp, ServoStyleSet.cpp, and supporting files).\n\nThe style resolution pipeline flows from ServoStyleSet as the main entry point, through RestyleManager for change tracking and scheduling, across the FFI boundary via ServoBindings functions into the Servo engine for style computation, and back through the Gecko layout system for frame styling."
}

